Note that cross-building for arm64 on x64 doesn't work yet. After this PR, I will work on https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues/74929 in cooperation with @christopherfujino :)

I figured out how to do it:
```
  testWidgets('Dropdown form field - default elevation', (WidgetTester tester) async {
    final Key buttonKey = UniqueKey();
    debugDisableShadows = false;
    await tester.pumpWidget(buildFormFrame(
      buttonKey: buttonKey,
      items: menuItems,
    ));
    await tester.tap(find.byKey(buttonKey));
    await tester.pumpAndSettle();

    final BoxShadow boxShadowOne = kElevationToShadow[8][0];
    final BoxShadow boxShadowTwo = kElevationToShadow[8][1];
    final BoxShadow boxShadowThree = kElevationToShadow[8][2];

    const Rect originalRectangle = Rect.fromLTRB(0.0, 0.0, 800, 208.0);
    final RRect rrectOne = RRect.fromRectAndRadius(
      originalRectangle.shift(
        boxShadowOne.offset
      ).inflate(boxShadowOne.spreadRadius),
      const Radius.circular(2.0),
    );
    final RRect rrectTwo = RRect.fromRectAndRadius(
      originalRectangle.shift(
        boxShadowTwo.offset
      ).inflate(boxShadowTwo.spreadRadius),
      const Radius.circular(2.0),
    );
    final RRect rrectThree = RRect.fromRectAndRadius(
      originalRectangle.shift(
        boxShadowThree.offset
      ).inflate(boxShadowThree.spreadRadius),
      const Radius.circular(2.0),
    );

    final Finder customPaint = find.ancestor(
      of: find.text('one').last,
      matching: find.byType(CustomPaint),
    ).last;

    expect(
      customPaint,
      paints
        ..save()
        ..rrect(rrect: rrectOne, color: boxShadowOne.color, hasMaskFilter: true)
        ..rrect(rrect: rrectTwo, color: boxShadowTwo.color, hasMaskFilter: true)
        ..rrect(rrect: rrectThree, color: boxShadowThree.color, hasMaskFilter: true),
    );
    debugDisableShadows = true;
  });
```

Please make a test for custom elevation as well. If you can, see if you can simplify the logic as well.
